content: Extra long review since you're an indie! Good game. The gameplay itself is well-executed and there weren't any bugs or glitches that I came across. Puzzles are fun and have a good balance between obvious and cryptic. The voice acting is okay. The girl's is very well done but the male voices are a bit exaggerated and the tone doesn't match the situation they are in. Two critiques though. *minor spoilers* First, when you go into the bedroom the main character asks if she remembers having sleepovers and her response is "that's why I never go down there". Odd..but ok. Later on the main character talks about how creepy the shelter is and she has the same exact response. I think the latter makes sense and the former is the wrong dialogue response. Second, in the sections that have the "my furture self is the past of my brother whatever" puzzles. I had no idea those were two separate floors. It just looked like the door was half open. I eventually had to find a walkthrough to see that was what I was missing. Consider making delineating the floors a little better. I also had max brightness on. Cheers~
replyContent:
Thanks for the review!

Re: the 1st issue, the "that's why I never go down there" is implying that yes, she does remember the sleepovers, and never lived them, so chooses not to go down there now. And the reason she didn't like them is specified in the second response of it being "creepy".

Re: the 2nd issue, you're right about the floors, thanks!

A pretty poor and uninspired take on a puzzler similar to The Room without anywhere near the class, polish, graphics, originality or quality. Throws in a tacky generic zombie story that bursts in from time to time over a walkie talkie but offers zero in the way of drama. The voice acting from your character is some of the worst i have heard and the talking scenes serve more to kill the mood. The puzzles are fun and some are quite clever but this is a game that would be better served free. Hell, they could use the radio in the bedroom to play ads for sponsors, pay extra to find the off switch if you want. I cracked the whole thing in about an hour and a half and paid for this. I spent the same time on Telltales Walking Dead episode one and i have spent 30+hrs on Real Racing. This does not feel like value for money.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback, we appreciate it. We are a company of just two people and thus our games aren't necessarily as polished as games that have dozens of people working on and budgets to match. In regards to the game being free, we choose to charge for our games so that we can pay rent and buy food.
